column5: Well with all this white stuff and the colder temps. Plus the boat being out side.  I may have to STORE the boat this year.  This will be the first time in 6 year.  When it was in the garage, all I had to do was condition the fuel and the boat was ready to go at any time.
Na worries . Get that gas auger ready and you wont miss the boat at all.
hmmm wish I could worry about maybe using my boat, the bays been frooze over for weeks and my Mako already has a 4 ft snowbank in front of it
